00:24:52,221 --> 00:24:55,783
[SPEAKER_01]: I hadn't been to it before, so I was surprised by the number of people who came through.

314
00:24:57,094 --> 00:25:02,860
[SPEAKER_01]: And especially the number of people who stopped at our table to talk to us.

315
00:25:02,940 --> 00:25:13,732
[SPEAKER_01]: They seemed very interested in things like the mass save home energy assessments and more information about the aggregation.

316
00:25:15,989 --> 00:25:17,690
[SPEAKER_01]: Is that what you saw too, Bob?

317
00:25:17,710 --> 00:25:19,130
[SPEAKER_01]: We trade it off sometimes.

318
00:25:19,210 --> 00:25:27,173
[SPEAKER_07]: Some people said, well, I would like to do this project, but even to get started, I had to spend $6,000 to fix my knob and tube wiring.

319
00:25:27,253 --> 00:25:30,053
[SPEAKER_07]: So how could I even proceed?

320
00:25:30,114 --> 00:25:34,695
[SPEAKER_07]: So there's a lot of financial roadblocks on getting this done.

321
00:25:34,715 --> 00:25:42,017
[SPEAKER_07]: A heat pump system where you want to put in the insulation, but you can't put the insulation in if you have to do an electrical upgrade.

322
00:25:42,958 --> 00:25:43,858
[SPEAKER_07]: And so, you know,

323
00:25:45,723 --> 00:25:51,107
[SPEAKER_07]: It's, there's a lot of financial challenges to this climate change stuff.

324
00:25:52,929 --> 00:26:08,941
[SPEAKER_01]: I also think that's a, that's, that emphasizes sort of how important it is to get information out there, because for instance, for Novantube wiring, there are, there is funding available for barrier mitigation for things like that through, through the MassAve program.

325
00:26:09,021 --> 00:26:14,565
[SPEAKER_01]: So, um, just sort of the more details about things like that, that we can get out there, the better.

326
00:26:16,648 --> 00:26:23,595
[SPEAKER_07]: So that was it was good to get some experiences like this because I will help us to better educate.

327
00:26:24,597 --> 00:26:28,220
[SPEAKER_07]: Our citizens are you know of Medford.

