00:47:30,000 --> 00:47:33,942
[SPEAKER_10]: So I'm just like to comment that.

529
00:47:35,062 --> 00:47:45,386
[SPEAKER_10]: Responding to various comment about the replacement, appropriate replacement for a 30 inch tree, I have once in my career replaced a 30 inch tree.

530
00:47:47,602 --> 00:48:04,670
[SPEAKER_10]: It was replaced because the alumni of Simmons College were so upset about cutting down a beach that they raised the exorbitant amount of money it took to move a large tree rather than replacing it with a smaller tree.

531
00:48:04,690 --> 00:48:07,391
[SPEAKER_10]: And I think you have to recognize that there's a

532
00:48:08,702 --> 00:48:17,525
[SPEAKER_10]: The cost of increasing the caliper size of the tree does not increase proportionally the cost of planting.

533
00:48:18,105 --> 00:48:19,725
[SPEAKER_10]: It increases exponentially.

534
00:48:20,566 --> 00:48:33,010
[SPEAKER_10]: So you will not realistically find a replacement for a 30-inch tree that is affordable within the context of a development.

535
00:48:35,435 --> 00:48:37,736
[SPEAKER_09]: I'm not saying that though.

536
00:48:37,796 --> 00:48:42,937
[SPEAKER_09]: I was saying equivalent numbers as small trees would need to be larger.

537
00:48:43,577 --> 00:48:46,738
[SPEAKER_10]: No, yeah, yeah, yeah, I do agree with that.

538
00:48:46,758 --> 00:48:48,838
[SPEAKER_10]: But I think I would just caution that we can't.

539
00:48:51,199 --> 00:49:04,002
[SPEAKER_10]: The math is a little more complex than just taking the the area of the existing tree and and using that as a basis.

540
00:49:05,713 --> 00:49:11,475
[SPEAKER_10]: I do think, I do think it's good that the group, the council split this into three ordinances.

541
00:49:11,575 --> 00:49:15,016
[SPEAKER_10]: It makes it much more manageable to deal with.

542
00:49:17,977 --> 00:49:26,820
[SPEAKER_10]: And I do think that the exemption or at least mitigation for affordable housing is appropriate.

