[SPEAKER_11]: You mean us?

832
01:18:06,406 --> 01:18:06,986
[SPEAKER_11]: Yes, you guys.

833
01:18:07,026 --> 01:18:07,366
[SPEAKER_11]: Sorry.

834
01:18:10,867 --> 01:18:15,888
[SPEAKER_11]: We are in touch with the Conservation Commission.

835
01:18:15,968 --> 01:18:21,990
[SPEAKER_00]: Because I know that they have situations where they need to permit trees to be taken down for various reasons.

836
01:18:22,050 --> 01:18:26,171
[SPEAKER_00]: There's actually a dam safety reason right now that they're going to be taking those.

837
01:18:26,271 --> 01:18:28,312
[SPEAKER_00]: Yes, they said they can talk to you guys about it.

838
01:18:29,552 --> 01:18:33,533
[SPEAKER_00]: But they came up with a ratio of replacement for those trees.

839
01:18:33,973 --> 01:18:48,437
[SPEAKER_00]: So the trees that are being removed because of dam safety reasons, the Winchester Dam, they're gonna be replacing, I think it's 40 trees around the city of Medford, but it's not even a one-for-one replacement that they're requiring.

840
01:18:49,277 --> 01:18:57,799
[SPEAKER_00]: So I just, I put that forward that it's perhaps a useful conversation to have explicitly with them is why are they using the ratio they're using?

841
01:19:01,710 --> 01:19:28,177
[SPEAKER_14]: One of the things that we have brought up at MIF and the Indian Environment Committee is, and this was supported in the past year anyways, is having an ordinance, or I don't know what ordinance it would be in, or if it's a separate ordinance, is having these three companies,

842
01:19:30,232 --> 01:19:40,642
[SPEAKER_14]: being registered with the city, be certified avarice, and have requirements just like other contractors in the city have to.

843
01:19:41,462 --> 01:19:43,444
[SPEAKER_14]: And I think Barry and I talked about this.

844
01:19:44,285 --> 01:19:46,367
[SPEAKER_14]: I don't understand why.

845
01:19:48,008 --> 01:19:53,093
[SPEAKER_14]: I've had some neighbors have three different tree companies come out for the same trees.

846
01:19:53,755 --> 01:19:55,556
[SPEAKER_14]: because they weren't done right to begin with.

847
01:19:55,856 --> 01:20:01,419
[SPEAKER_14]: And some they lost because they trimmed more than 35% of the tree and the tree died, which is not recommended.

848
01:20:02,260 --> 01:20:06,542
[SPEAKER_14]: And I don't think that's a hard thing to ask.

849
01:20:06,662 --> 01:20:11,665
[SPEAKER_14]: So I would highly recommend that somehow we recommend that.

850
01:20:11,905 --> 01:20:16,368
[SPEAKER_14]: I'm not sure if we put this in one of the comments.

851
01:20:20,075 --> 01:20:27,657
[SPEAKER_14]: when we're writing back to the City Council, the MedFed Energy and Environment Committee, that they have to register.

852
01:20:27,677 --> 01:20:44,222
[SPEAKER_14]: You know, if they're filing the permits, which we're requiring the permits for tree removals and tree pruning on landmark trees, that they're filing a permit and they're registered.

853
01:20:45,062 --> 01:20:45,822
[SPEAKER_14]: They're certified.

854
01:20:45,842 --> 01:20:47,203
[SPEAKER_14]: They have insurance.

855
01:20:47,683 --> 01:20:48,503
[SPEAKER_14]: They know what they're doing.

856
01:20:50,223 --> 01:20:52,765
[SPEAKER_14]: Any comments about that from the committee?

857
01:20:54,307 --> 01:20:56,789
[SPEAKER_14]: Who's going to enforce it, Loretta?

858
01:20:57,830 --> 01:20:59,492
[SPEAKER_14]: And can we enforce it?

859
01:21:00,913 --> 01:21:10,282
[SPEAKER_14]: They're filing the permit, right, with the building commission, commissioner, office, the building department to remove trees, right?

860
01:21:10,972 --> 01:21:12,493
[SPEAKER_13]: That's ones that are filing.

861
01:21:12,573 --> 01:21:23,561
[SPEAKER_13]: What do we do about somebody who calls and says, I'm worried about these trees in my yard, they might fall on my house and have them removed, like Alicia's neighbor?

862
01:21:24,421 --> 01:21:32,527
[SPEAKER_09]: I mean, we deal with it the same way we deal with somebody who wasn't a licensed plumber replacing a heating system.

863
01:21:33,517 --> 01:21:35,922
[SPEAKER_09]: Well, I think it's just internal.

864
01:21:36,884 --> 01:21:41,353
[SPEAKER_13]: Somebody's got to complain to bring it to the attention of the city.

865
01:21:42,984 --> 01:21:52,813
[SPEAKER_14]: Well, OK, that's that's why a lot of this ordinance has been delayed because of my opinion, because of all these little details.

866
01:21:53,394 --> 01:21:55,796
[SPEAKER_14]: The idea is to get the ordinance done.

867
01:21:56,196 --> 01:21:56,476
[SPEAKER_14]: Yes.

868
01:21:56,496 --> 01:22:01,341
[SPEAKER_14]: How are they going to do it can be suggested to them, but it's not possible.

869
01:22:01,781 --> 01:22:05,485
[SPEAKER_14]: OK, so if I'm an electrician, I have to file a permit.

870
01:22:06,143 --> 01:22:06,443
[SPEAKER_14]: Right?

871
01:22:09,584 --> 01:22:18,987
[SPEAKER_14]: Most electricians or a tree contractor will have a letter that the city sends out saying these are the new requirements in Medford.

872
01:22:19,828 --> 01:22:28,411
[SPEAKER_14]: And they can have a list and find the list, the city of all the tree companies or and landscape providers.

873
01:22:29,511 --> 01:22:33,612
[SPEAKER_14]: So it'd be well documented to those companies our requirements.

874
01:22:34,253 --> 01:22:35,133
[SPEAKER_14]: That's the first step.

875
01:22:36,090 --> 01:22:37,130
[SPEAKER_14]: That's not a lot of work.

876
01:22:38,511 --> 01:22:52,237
[SPEAKER_12]: And to Barry's point, I would just add, fortunately, unlike plumbing or electricity, electrical work inside of a house, tree work is very noticeable.

877
01:22:53,917 --> 01:23:04,682
[SPEAKER_12]: And so if a neighbor who knows that there must be a permit is able to say, I think that there's somebody who's taking down trees without a permit, that would be

878
01:23:06,719 --> 01:23:15,008
[SPEAKER_12]: A. A report that could be reasonably like, we could have an easy path to reporting.

879
01:23:15,028 --> 01:23:20,754
[SPEAKER_12]: Um, any issues yeah, I was thinking a little more than.

880
01:23:22,714 --> 01:23:26,799
[SPEAKER_14]: not so much that of, you know, unreported tree removals.

881
01:23:27,640 --> 01:23:35,489
[SPEAKER_14]: I'm thinking more of the responsibility of the type of company that's coming into the city doing the work.

882
01:23:35,610 --> 01:23:36,691
[SPEAKER_14]: I agree with you on that.

883
01:23:36,771 --> 01:23:37,292
[SPEAKER_14]: Absolutely.

884
01:23:37,312 --> 01:23:42,418
[SPEAKER_14]: I think that for us, because this gets all over the place, I know you know what I'm talking about, but for others,

885
01:23:42,818 --> 01:23:53,156
[SPEAKER_14]: It's targeting the quality of the tree companies coming in and their responsibility to act within ISA certification arborist guidelines.

886
01:23:54,183 --> 01:24:17,677
[SPEAKER_14]: and not the hack-a-lots that are causing so much damage or landslides, which have happened in Medford because of tree companies in Colton Heights and up near the high school and horrific things that end up costing the city and the taxpayers more money because it's our property taxes and rents that are paying for this mitigation.

887
01:24:17,777 --> 01:24:21,959
[SPEAKER_14]: If you agree, where do we put that?

888
01:24:24,533 --> 01:24:30,134
[SPEAKER_14]: Does that go in the letter to the city council that we highly recommend this?

